# Copy to .env and fill from your Supabase project (Settings → API).
# The anon key is safe in the browser; RLS controls access. These power the
# live catalogue read, lead capture, and the Orty chatbot (via Edge Function).
# They are also read at BUILD time by scripts/prerender.mjs so SEO reflects the
# live catalogue — set them wherever you run `npm run build`.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# --- Orty chatbot ---
# The Gemini key is NOT set here. It lives server-side as a Supabase Edge
# Function secret (the site is fully static and has no server of its own):
#   supabase functions deploy orty-chat
#   supabase secrets set GEMINI_API_KEY=your-google-ai-studio-key
# The widget calls the orty-chat Edge Function; on any error it falls back to
# its built-in FAQ knowledge base.
